<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1574,1742]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,304,1574,1599]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe up to 
<number box="[460,490,1574,1598]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="57.0">57</number>
°N, absent from Scandinavia and 
<collectingCountry box="[861,942,1574,1598]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Britain</collectingCountry>
, in the east the distribution area goes to Ural River, present in North Africa: 
<collectingCountry box="[501,605,1611,1634]" name="Morocco" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[616,700,1610,1634]" name="Algeria" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Algeria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke" box="[714,882,1610,1634]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Warncke, K. (1992) Die Westpalaarktischen Arten der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Halictinae). Bericht der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft Augsburg, 52, 9 - 64." type="journal article" year="1992">
Warncke 
<number box="[822,882,1610,1634]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1574,1742]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1646,1671]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Biology.</emphasis>
Species of warmer open or shrubby habitats (forest steppes), common on loess walls. In central Europe quite rare, more abundant only at xerothermes. The only known host is 
<taxonomicName box="[1066,1285,1683,1707]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis box="[1066,1285,1683,1707]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Halictus maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, recorded by Stoeckhert (
<number box="[285,343,1718,1742]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1933.0">1933</number>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bluthgen" box="[406,593,1718,1742]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Bluthgen, P. (1934) Die Wirte der Palaarktischen Sphecodes - Arten. Zeitschrift Wissenschaftlicher Insekten-Biologie, 27, 33 - 42, 61 - 66. Bluthgen, P. (1935) Halictus, Nomioides und Sphecodes, pp. 360 - 367. In: Popov, V. V. (ed.) Beitrage zur Bienenfauna von Tadzhikistan. Trudy Tajikskoy Bazy Akademie Nauk SSSR, 5, 1 - 408." type="book chapter" year="1934">
Blüthgen (
<number box="[524,585,1718,1742]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1934.0">1934</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. We have only observed 
<taxonomicName box="[873,1017,1718,1742]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufiventris">
<emphasis box="[873,1017,1718,1742]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">S. rufiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in association with this species.
</paragraph>
